Read the camera manufacturer's quantum efficiency (%) file and interpolate to the wavelengths we are interested in. 

```python
import pandas as pd

QE = pd.read_csv(f"assets/CRED3_30C.csv",names=["wavelength","QE_pct"], header=None)
QE.insert(0,"type","manufacturer")
QE = pd.concat( [ pd.DataFrame({"type":"6SV","wavelength":wavelengths_nm}), QE] )
QE.set_index("wavelength",inplace=True)
QE.interpolate(method="cubicspline",axis="index",limit_direction="both",inplace=True)
QE = QE[QE["type"].str.match("6SV")]
QE.drop("type", 1,inplace=True)
QE_array = QE["QE_pct"].to_numpy()/100

QE.plot()
```

```python

def snr_curve(f_num=4,integration_time_ms=80,pixel_len_Î¼m=15,bandwidth_nm=0.5,surface_reflectance=.3,optical_trans_efficiency=0.65):
    
    N = ref_model.photons * integration_time_ms*1e-3 * pixel_len_Î¼m**2 * np.pi/(2*f_num)**2 * \
                    bandwidth_nm*1e-3 * QE_array * optical_trans_efficiency * surface_reflectance
    
    table = hv.Table((wavelengths_nm[N>=0]/1e3, np.sqrt(N[N>=0])), 'wavelength (Î¼m)', 'SNR')
    return hv.Curve(table).opts(tools=["hover"],width=600,height=350,ylim=(0,None))


dmap = hv.DynamicMap(snr_curve, kdims=["f_num","integration_time_ms","pixel_len_Î¼m",
                                       "bandwidth_nm","surface_reflectance","optical_trans_efficiency"])
dmap.redim.range(f_num=(1,10), integration_time_ms=(1,100), pixel_len_Î¼m=(1,30),
                bandwidth_nm=(0.1,10),surface_reflectance=(0.1,1.),optical_trans_efficiency=(0.5,1.))
```
